<PB N="271" REF="276">
<HEAD>Virgilius Re&s;tauratus: SEU MARTINI SCRIBLERI, Summi Critici, Ca&s;tigationum in Aeneidem SPECIMEN.</HEAD>
<P>AENEIDEM totam, Amice Lector, innumerabilibus poene mendis &s;caturientem, ad pri&s;tinum &s;en|&s;um revocabimus. In &s;ingulis fere ver&s;ibus &s;puriae occurrunt lectiones, in omnibus quos un|quam vidi codicibus, aut vulgatis aut ineditis, ad opprobrium u&s;que Criticorum, in hunc diem exi&s;tentes. Interea adverte oculos, et his pau|cis fruere. At &s;i quae &s;int in hi&s;ce ca&s;tigationi|bus, de quibus non &s;atis liquet, &s;yllabarum quan|titates, <GAP DESC="FOREIGN"> no&s;tra Libro ip&s;i praefigen|da, ut con&s;ulas, moneo.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1>
<PB N="272" REF="277">
<HEAD>I. SPECIMEN LIBRI PRIMI,</HEAD>
