<P>But $$mesis, who delights in $word$ the best laid designs of $upid, ma$ie$ously contrired the means to make these three Lovers unhappy.&punc; S$s$$ner had the Master of the Shew $word$ n$lice of $word$ flight, but he seiz'd on the Boh$ mian Ladies by $$arrant; and not content with having recover'd the pe$$$si$n of them, reselr'd to open all the S$$i$$s of the Saw upon. Martin&punc; So he instantly went to counsel to adrise upon all po&s;sible methods of Revenge.</P>
<P>The first point he preceed$$ on was the Property of his Monster, and the question prepeunded was <NOTE N="1" PLACE="foot">An Sewi po$sin$, in vitis Dominis, Matrimonium contrahere?</NOTE><Q>&startq;Whether Slaves could marry without the consent of their Master?&endq;</Q> To this he was answer'd in the Affirmative, but told at the same time <Q>&startq;That <NOTE N="2" PLACE="foot">An Se$us Matrimonio $$imit$$ a Demini obsequie?</NOTE>the Marriage did not exempt them from Servitude.&endq;</Q></P>
