<P>Then his Counsel judged it more advisable to plead for a $i&s;solution of the Marriage, upon the impo&s;sibility of Conjugal du$s in the $ife. But then the $anen Law al|low'd a Jriennial $ehabitation; which intirely ruin'd this project also. Besides it was evident by the same. Law, that "Monstrosity could not incapacitate from Marriage," witne&s;s the Case of Hermaphrodites, who are allow'd "facultation Conjug&uuml;, provided they make Election be|fore the Parish Priest, in what for they will act, and take an $a$$ never to perform in the other Capacity." <NOTE N="1" PLACE="foot">Sanchez, Hostiens. Sybrest.</NOTE>It was consulted whether Martin should not be per|mitted to take away his Wife since, upon his so doing "he might be s$ed for a hape upon the Body of her &s;is|ter, there being plainly the four Conditions of a<NOTE N="2" PLACE="foot">$identia, Causa Litidinis, Traduclio ad L$$um, Mulier honesta.</NOTE>Ra&s;$e".
