<P>Wereupon Martin was reduc'd to turn Plaintiff, and commenc'd a Suit in the Spiritual Court against the black Prince, for Cohabitation with his said Wife. He was advis'd to insist upon a n$w point, (viz.) <Q>&startq;That Lindamira and Indamora together made up but one lawful Wife.&endq;</Q></P>
<P>The Monster-master, further to distre&s;s Martin, forc'd Sin|damira to petition for $$ment, $word$ pendente: which was no sooner allow'd her by the Court, but he obliged her to alledge, that, <Q>&startq;it was not sufficient to maintain both her|self and her Sister; and if her Sister perish'd, she could not live with the dead Body about her.&endq;</Q></P>
