<P>We cannot wonder that he contracted a violent $ver|sion to the $aw, as is evident from a whole Chapter of his Travels. And perhaps his Disappointment gave him also a Dis-inelination to the Fair Sex, for whom on some occasions he does not expre&s;s all the Respect and admiration po&s;sible. This doubtless must be the Reason; that i$ no part of his we find him $$ee'd by any strange Prince&s;s; $er have we $he least account that he ever relaps'd into this Pa&s;|sion, except what is mentioned in the Introduction, of the Spanish' Lady's Phenomenon.</P>
